reviewText: Beautiful,  like  taking a trip myself.

This short film is a great introduction to one of the great scenic areas of western Cuba. The area has become fairly popular and you can see why. It's also a key tobacco growing region and that brings other tourists so do not expect an out-of-the-way kind of place. This area is close enough to Havana to do a great overnight trip if you rent a car.
Considering the difficulties of filming in Cuba, I consider it a good video. Perhaps, the script should reflect more research.

this is a refreshing show of Cuba so often a country is only shown with the representation of the terrorist "Presidente"  Cuba is an enchanting country with lots of beautiful intelligent individuals it is time we start focusing on that
